<seg id=1> Foreign Investment in Jiangsu Agriculture Increasing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Nanjing, December 16, Telegram (Reporter Zhou Fang).  Foreign investment in agriculture in Jiangsu Province is increasing daily. </seg>
<seg id=3> Currently, there are 800 agricultural projects in Jiangsu Province receiving direct foreign investment in a total amount of more than US$800 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> An official of the Jiangsu Provincial Agriculture and Forestry Department states that since 1994, more than 500 "three-capital" enterprises employing more than US$700 million in foreign capital have been approved by the Jiangsu provincial agriculture system, amounting to three times and seven times the pre-1993 levels, respectively. </seg>
<seg id=5> The increase in foreign capital from the U.S., Japan, and Singapore has been the largest.  The investment ratio of foreign firms in new projects has been rising, with sole proprietorship enterprises showing a marked increase. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The rapid increase in foreign capital has to a large extent compensated for [otherwise] inadequate investment in the agriculture of Jiangsu Province. </seg>
<seg id=7> Accordingly to statistics, there are currently more than one hundred agricultural and sideline product processing enterprises with a production value of more than RMB100 million in Jiangsu Province. </seg>
<seg id=8> The Ruyi Group of Lianyun Harbor has used loans from the Japanese government and direct foreign investment to build what is currently the vegetable processing and sales enterprise with the highest level of exports and the greatest variety of products in China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Jiangsu has also used foreign capital to introduce nearly one hundred superior types of beer barley, California perch, Roe marsh shrimp, breeding chickens, lean meat swine, vegetables, flowers, and plants, as well as modern production and processing techniques, significantly enhancing the level of agricultural production. </seg>
</p>
